content.description: The best Sandstone in Wisconsin!  Stand Start with right hand on pebble and left hand on bad sloper.  Use horrible feet and slap up the slopey aretes to gain a good hold at top.  Very unique for the area.
content.location: This boulder is located a little above the road well below the Old Sandstone climbing area.

content.description: You won't find better sandstone anywhere.  Bullet hard and extremely difficult, this is a fantastic project.  Sit start with obvious holds under right arete roof.  Use small holds and slopers to make it to the good holds on lip.  You can see all the moves on this problem, they are just really hard!  Get on it.
content.location: Best way to approach the Rebel Pride boulder is from the road.  Walk a few hundred feet to the east from the Old Sandstone parking area and then cut strait up into the woods.  The boulder is a few hundred feet up from the road.

content.description: Sit start just left of Twoarete syndrome on the Rebel Pride boulder.  Make a difficult first move to two quartzite pebbles.  Continue to the top.  Not a bad warm-up.

Excellent sandstone, hidden in the woods but close to the road.

 Called "Huevos Rancheros" in Bonamici.
